        <p class="TableText">You can use the drop-down arrow in this field to select a factory medium (e.g., non-print, print) or a medium that you have created. A medium is a feature that lets you produce an alternative set of styles in a stylesheet, which you can use for different outputs. They are intended to be an exception to the default style you want to use. You can select a medium in the list and then set property values for it in the Stylesheet Editor. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Styles/Mediums/About_Stylesheet_Mediums.htm">About Stylesheet Mediums</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
